{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2015}} '''Dieudonné Kabongo''' (1950 &ndash; October 11, 2011) was a [[Democratic Republic of the Congo|Congolese]]-born Belgian comedian, humorist, musician and actor. Kabongo co-starred in the 2000 film, ''[[Lumumba (film)|Lumumba]]'', portraying [[Godefroid Munongo]].<ref name=pana>{{cite news|first= |last= |title=Belgium: Congolese actor Dieudonnné Kabongo dies on stage |url=http://www.afriquejet.com/belgium-congolese-actor-2011101324865.html |work=[[PanaPress]] |publisher=[[Afrique en ligne]] |date=October 13, 2011 |accessdate=2011-10-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120614064819/http://www.afriquejet.com/belgium-congolese-actor-2011101324865.html |archivedate=June 14, 2012 |df=mdy }}</ref> He was the first comedian of African descent to achieve widespread popularity in [[Belgium]].<ref name=afrika>{{cite news |first= |last= |title=Dieudonné Kabongo, A Great Actor Died on Stage |url=http://www.afrikafilmfestival.be/en/home/item/115-dieudonn%C3%A9-kabongo-overleden-tijdens-show-in-jette |work=[[Afrika Filmfestival]] |publisher= |date=October 13, 2011 |accessdate=2011-10-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111203121902/http://www.afrikafilmfestival.be/en/home/item/115-dieudonn%C3%A9-kabongo-overleden-tijdens-show-in-jette |archivedate=December 3, 2011 |df=mdy }}</ref><ref name=courier>{{cite news |first=Hegel |last=Goutier |title=A day in the life of Dieudonné Kabongo |url=http://www.acp-eucourier.info/Um-dia-na-vida-de-Di.168.0.html%3F%2526L%3D0 |work=[[The Courier (ACP-EU)]] |publisher= |date=December 2007 |accessdate=2011-10-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111218205854/http://acp-eucourier.info/Um-dia-na-vida-de-Di.168.0.html%3F%2526L%3D0 |archivedate=December 18, 2011 |df=mdy }}</ref>
== Biography == Kabongo was born in 1950 in [[Katanga Province|Katanga]], [[Belgian Congo]], which is now the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]].<ref name=pana/> He immigrated to Belgium in 1970.<ref name=afrika/> He originally studied electromechanical engineering in [[Virton]], [[Belgium]], before embarking on a self-apprenticeship in theater and writing.<ref name=courier/>
In 1984, Kabongo and fellow actor [[Mirko Popovitch]] jointly won the First Prize at the [[Festival International du Rire de Rochefort]].<ref name=pana/><ref name=afrika/> His film credits included ''[[Identity Pieces]]'' in 1998, the 2000 film ''[[Lumumba (film)|Lumumba]]'', directed by [[Raoul Peck]], and the 2005 film, ''[[Le Couperet]]'', directed by [[Costa-Gavras]].<ref name=pana/><ref name=afrika/> He was awarded the lifetime achievement award by the Africa Filmfestival in 2010.<ref name=afrika/> For his role in ''[[The Invader (2011 film)|The Invader]]'', he received a [[Magritte Award]] nomination for [[Magritte Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]].
Kabongo collapsed and died during a performance on stage at a [[cultural center]] in [[Jette]], a district of [[Brussels]], on October 11, 2011, at the age of 61.<ref name=pana/>
